<?php $__env->startSection('content'); ?><p>Bayern Munich have won the German Super Cup after beating Borussia Dortmund in a pulsating game at the Allianz Arena.</p>

<p>Hansi Flick's side took a two-goal lead through Corentin Tolisso and Thomas Muller but goals from Julian Brandt and Erling Haaland brought Dortmund level.</p>

<p>But Bayern's ruthless streak continued as Joshua Kimmich popped up to score a fortunate 82nd minute winner to hand Bayern their second trophy of the season.  </p>

<p>More to follow. </p>

<p>Bayern Munich have won the German Super Cup after beating Borussia Dortmund</p>

<p>Joshua Kimmich (on the floor) scored a fortunate winner for Bayern at the Allianz Arena</p>

<p>Bayern took the lead after 18 minutes when Corentin Tolisso fired home from very close range</p>

<p>Tolisso celebrates with Alphonso Davies after he finished off a slick Bayern Munich counter</p>

<p>Thomas Muller doubled the Bayern Munich lead as they looked to be in cruise control early on</p>

<p>But Dortmund were not two goals behind for long as Julian Brandt (L) reduced the deficit</p>

<p>Erling Haaland made it 2-2 early on in the second half with an assured left-footed finish</p>

<p>The Norwegian wonderkid celebrates with team-mates Marco Reus and Thomas Delaney</p>

<p>Bayern: Neuer, Pavard (Richards 76), Sule, Martinez (Musiala 84), Hernandez, Kimmich, Tolisso, Coman (Gnabry 54), Muller, Davies, Lewandowski (Zirkzee 83).</p>

<p>Subs not used: Boateng, Alaba, Fein, Nubel, Tillman</p>

<p>Goals: Tolisso 18, Muller 32, Kimmich 82</p>

<p>Booked: Hernandez</p>

<p>Manager: Hansi Flick</p>

<p>Dortmund: Hitz, Can, Hummels (Piszczek 76), Akanji, Meunier (Schulz 67), Dahoud, Delaney, Passlack, Reus (Reyna 72), Brandt (Bellingham 76), Haaland (Reinier 68).</p>

<p>Subs not used: Guerreiro, Wolf, Witsel, Drljaca</p>

<p>Goals: Brandt 39, Haaland 55 </p>

<p>Manager: Lucien Favre </p>

